\description{
Converts Analysis Results Data (ARD) from packages like
\href{https://insightsengineering.github.io/cards/}{cards} into a wide summary
data frame suitable for \code{\link[=fr_table]{fr_table()}}. ARD stores one row per statistic;
\code{fr_wide_ard()} combines statistics using format strings, pivots treatment
arms to columns, and returns a display-ready data frame.

This function has \strong{no dependency on cards} — it accepts any data frame
with the standard ARD columns (\code{variable}, \code{stat_name}, \code{stat}).

Handles all common post-\code{ard_stack()} pipeline shapes:
\itemize{
\item Raw \code{ard_stack()} output (list columns)
\item After \code{unlist_ard_columns()} (atomic columns)
\item After \code{rename_ard_columns(columns = all_ard_groups("names"))} (group
columns renamed to e.g. \code{ARM})
\item After default \code{rename_ard_columns()} (both groups and variables renamed)
\item Multi-group \code{.by = c(ARM, SEX)} — extra groups preserved in output
\item No \code{.by} at all (ungrouped)
}
